******
[2] Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region
Date: Sat 8 Jul 2017 19:40 PM
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19571.html


Xinjiang Construction Corp reported one human H7N9 AIV fatal case on [Fri 30 Jun 2017]. This is the 1st human H7N9 AIV case reported by Xinjiang Construstion Corp in 2017. The 35-year-old male patient, lived in Kuitun city. He had engaged in selling and slaughtering live chickens at local live poultry market with his parents. The patient had onset of ILI symptoms(fever, cough, sore throat, fatigue and shivering) on [Fri 23 Jun 2017], he was reported as suspected human H7N9 case on [Thu 29 Jun 2017], his samples tested positive for H7N9 by CDC on [Fri 30 Jun 2017] and he subsequently passed away that night due to respiratory failure. All close contacts are under medical monitoring.

--
